The paper deals with the problem of revenue maximization in auctions, which is a classic topic in computational game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design (cs.EC). The use of optimal transport duality to derive lower bounds is a technique from information theory (cs.IT) and optimization (cs.DS). The paper also involves analyzing the communication complexity of mechanisms, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
